  '["Hannah praises the LORD for overturning the proud and lifting the humble, setting the tone for the whole book. The chapter then contrasts her faith with the corruption of Eli''s sons, who abuse sacrifices and despise the LORD''s offering. Samuel grows before God while a man of God warns Eli that his house will be judged for dishonoring the sanctuary.", "Hannah pours out her grief before the LORD at Shiloh and vows that if God gives her a son she will dedicate him to lifelong service. Eli misreads her silent prayer at first, then blesses her, and the LORD opens her womb. Samuel is born, weaned, and brought to the sanctuary as a living answer to prayer.", "Samuel hears the LORD calling in the night, and after Eli''s help he learns to answer, \"Speak, for your servant hears.\" The message confirms judgment on Eli''s house and cannot be hidden. Samuel grows into a trustworthy prophet whose words are established throughout Israel.", "The Philistines send the ark back on a new cart with guilt offerings, testing whether the plague came from God or chance. The cows head straight for Beth-shemesh, confirming that the LORD is guiding the return. Israel rejoices but also learns reverence when some men look into the ark and are struck down."]'::jsonb,
  'Hannah praises the LORD for overturning the proud and lifting the humble, setting the tone for the whole book. The chapter then contrasts her faith with the corruption of Eli''s sons, who abuse sacrifices and despise the LORD''s offering. Samuel grows before God while a man of God warns Eli that his house will be judged for dishonoring the sanctuary.',
  'This advanced summary best matches 1 Samuel 2 (1 Samuel 2:1-10-1 Samuel 2:1-36).'
