  'Which advanced summary best matches 1 Samuel 5?',
  '["The Philistines place the ark in Dagon''s temple, but Dagon falls before it and the people are struck with affliction. Town after town suffers because the ark brings the LORD''s presence into enemy territory. The chapter makes clear that the captured ark is not captive at all; it is still ruling.", "Israel treats the ark like a talisman and marches it into battle, but the Philistines rout the army and capture the ark. Eli falls backward and dies when he hears the news, and his daughter-in-law names her son Ichabod because the glory has departed from Israel. The chapter is a stark warning that sacred objects cannot replace covenant faithfulness.", "The Philistines send the ark back on a new cart with guilt offerings, testing whether the plague came from God or chance. The cows head straight for Beth-shemesh, confirming that the LORD is guiding the return. Israel rejoices but also learns reverence when some men look into the ark and are struck down.", "Saul searches for his father''s lost donkeys and is led by providence to Samuel instead. The LORD tells Samuel to anoint the man from Benjamin, and Samuel identifies Saul as the chosen one with honor at the feast. The chapter quietly introduces Saul as a tall and promising king-to-be, even before he knows it himself."]'::jsonb,
