  'Samuel anoints Saul, gives him signs, and tells him that the Spirit will come upon him as proof of God''s choice. Saul prophesies with the prophets, and the people marvel because the change is so unmistakable. Yet Saul also hides, hinting that his kingship will be marked by uncertainty as well as promise.',
