  5,
  'Which advanced summary best matches 1 Samuel 15?',
  '["Samuel commands Saul to destroy Amalek completely, but Saul spares the best livestock and keeps King Agag alive. When confronted, Saul blames the people, but Samuel declares that obedience is better than sacrifice and that the LORD has rejected Saul as king. The chapter ends with Agag''s death and Samuel''s grief over Saul''s failure.", "Jonathan and his armor bearer trust the LORD and spark a panic among the Philistines, showing that faith can win where armies hesitate. Saul''s rash oath, however, weakens the people and nearly costs Jonathan his life after the king''s own son tastes honey. The chapter contrasts brave initiative with foolish religion and ends with Saul''s damaged leadership.", "The LORD sends Samuel to Bethlehem to anoint a new king from Jesse''s sons, and David is chosen because the LORD looks on the heart. The Spirit comes upon David, while an evil spirit troubles Saul and leads to the introduction of David as a musician in the court. The chapter quietly begins the rise of Israel''s future king.", "Saul orders David killed, but Jonathan intercedes and briefly restores peace between them. When Saul''s rage returns, David escapes through a window and Michal helps him flee while pretending he is ill. The chapter shows how family ties and loyal friendship still cannot overcome Saul''s growing hostility."]'::jsonb,
  'Samuel commands Saul to destroy Amalek completely, but Saul spares the best livestock and keeps King Agag alive. When confronted, Saul blames the people, but Samuel declares that obedience is better than sacrifice and that the LORD has rejected Saul as king. The chapter ends with Agag''s death and Samuel''s grief over Saul''s failure.',
  'This advanced summary best matches 1 Samuel 15 (1 Samuel 15:1-9-1 Samuel 15:1-23).'
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
  SELECT 1 FROM quiz_question_bank
  WHERE book_number = 9
    AND chapter = 15
    AND difficulty_stage = 5
    AND prompt = 'Which advanced summary best matches 1 Samuel 15?'
);

