  'David comes to the battlefield with bread for his brothers and ends up facing Goliath, the giant who mocks the armies of the living God. David declares that the battle belongs to the LORD, strikes Goliath with a sling stone, and wins a decisive victory with the giant''s own sword. The chapter celebrates faith that sees God''s honor where others see only impossible odds.',
  'This summary line expresses the narrative function of 1 Samuel 17.'
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
  SELECT 1 FROM quiz_question_bank
  WHERE book_number = 9
    AND chapter = 17
    AND difficulty_stage = 4
    AND prompt = 'Which summary line best expresses the narrative function of 1 Samuel 17?'
);

