  9,
  20,
  3,
  'Which summary best fits the movement of 1 Samuel 20?',
  '["David and Jonathan use a secret sign at the feast to determine Saul''s intent, and Saul''s murderous anger is confirmed. The two friends renew their covenant and part with grief, knowing the kingdom''s conflict will separate them. The chapter deepens the tragedy by showing loyalty trapped inside royal violence.", "Saul orders David killed, but Jonathan intercedes and briefly restores peace between them. When Saul''s rage returns, David escapes through a window and Michal helps him flee while pretending he is ill. The chapter shows how family ties and loyal friendship still cannot overcome Saul''s growing hostility.", "David arrives at Nob hungry and receives the holy bread and Goliath''s sword from Ahimelech, but the encounter later costs the priests their lives. He then flees to Gath, where he pretends madness to survive among the Philistines. The chapter shows David in exile, scrambling for food, weapons, and safety while Saul''s violence expands.", "David gathers a band of distressed followers in the cave of Adullam while Saul''s suspicion turns into murderous paranoia. Doeg tells Saul that Ahimelech helped David, and the king orders the priests of Nob killed, deepening the bloodguilt on his house. Abiathar escapes to David, linking the outlaw king and the surviving priesthood."]'::jsonb,
  'David and Jonathan use a secret sign at the feast to determine Saul''s intent, and Saul''s murderous anger is confirmed. The two friends renew their covenant and part with grief, knowing the kingdom''s conflict will separate them. The chapter deepens the tragedy by showing loyalty trapped inside royal violence.',
  'This summary captures the movement of 1 Samuel 20 (1 Samuel 20:1-23-1 Samuel 20:1-23).'
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
  SELECT 1 FROM quiz_question_bank
  WHERE book_number = 9
    AND chapter = 20
    AND difficulty_stage = 3
    AND prompt = 'Which summary best fits the movement of 1 Samuel 20?'
);

