  5,
  'What final perspective best fits 1 Samuel 27?',
  '["David decides he will perish by Saul''s hand unless he finds refuge among the Philistines, so he settles in Ziklag under Achish. From there he raids surrounding peoples while telling Achish that he has struck Judah, keeping the king of Gath confident in his loyalty. The chapter captures David living by concealment and survival in enemy territory.", "Saul becomes desperate when the Philistines gather and the LORD no longer answers him, so he disguises himself and seeks a medium at Endor. The woman summons Samuel, who rebukes Saul and repeats that the LORD has torn the kingdom away from him. Saul hears the sentence of death before returning to face the battle.", "Hannah pours out her grief before the LORD at Shiloh and vows that if God gives her a son she will dedicate him to lifelong service. Eli misreads her silent prayer at first, then blesses her, and the LORD opens her womb. Samuel is born, weaned, and brought to the sanctuary as a living answer to prayer.", "Hannah praises the LORD for overturning the proud and lifting the humble, setting the tone for the whole book. The chapter then contrasts her faith with the corruption of Eli''s sons, who abuse sacrifices and despise the LORD''s offering. Samuel grows before God while a man of God warns Eli that his house will be judged for dishonoring the sanctuary."]'::jsonb,
  'David decides he will perish by Saul''s hand unless he finds refuge among the Philistines, so he settles in Ziklag under Achish. From there he raids surrounding peoples while telling Achish that he has struck Judah, keeping the king of Gath confident in his loyalty. The chapter captures David living by concealment and survival in enemy territory.',
  'This final perspective fits 1 Samuel 27 (1 Samuel 27:1-7-1 Samuel 27:1-7).'
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
  SELECT 1 FROM quiz_question_bank
  WHERE book_number = 9
    AND chapter = 27
    AND difficulty_stage = 5
