  '["Saul becomes desperate when the Philistines gather and the LORD no longer answers him, so he disguises himself and seeks a medium at Endor. The woman summons Samuel, who rebukes Saul and repeats that the LORD has torn the kingdom away from him. Saul hears the sentence of death before returning to face the battle.", "As the Philistines assemble for war, their lords distrust David and insist that he not march with them. Achish defends David''s loyalty, but the commanders fear he will turn against them in battle, so David is sent home from Aphek. The chapter frees David from an impossible battlefield alliance before the final crisis with Saul unfolds.", "While David and his men are away, Amalekites raid Ziklag, burn the city, and take the families captive. David strengthens himself in the LORD, pursues the raiders with divine guidance, and recovers everyone along with much spoil. The chapter ends with David sharing the recovered goods widely, showing both courage and generosity.", "The Philistines defeat Israel at Mount Gilboa, and Saul''s sons fall beside him. Wounded and unable to continue, Saul falls on his own sword after his armor bearer refuses to kill him, and the Philistines later display the bodies in shame. Men of Jabesh-gilead recover the remains and bury them with fasting, ending Saul''s reign in grief and honor."]'::jsonb,
  'Saul becomes desperate when the Philistines gather and the LORD no longer answers him, so he disguises himself and seeks a medium at Endor. The woman summons Samuel, who rebukes Saul and repeats that the LORD has torn the kingdom away from him. Saul hears the sentence of death before returning to face the battle.',
