  '["Saul becomes desperate when the Philistines gather and the LORD no longer answers him, so he disguises himself and seeks a medium at Endor. The woman summons Samuel, who rebukes Saul and repeats that the LORD has torn the kingdom away from him. Saul hears the sentence of death before returning to face the battle.", "David decides he will perish by Saul''s hand unless he finds refuge among the Philistines, so he settles in Ziklag under Achish. From there he raids surrounding peoples while telling Achish that he has struck Judah, keeping the king of Gath confident in his loyalty. The chapter captures David living by concealment and survival in enemy territory.", "As the Philistines assemble for war, their lords distrust David and insist that he not march with them. Achish defends David''s loyalty, but the commanders fear he will turn against them in battle, so David is sent home from Aphek. The chapter frees David from an impossible battlefield alliance before the final crisis with Saul unfolds.", "Hannah pours out her grief before the LORD at Shiloh and vows that if God gives her a son she will dedicate him to lifelong service. Eli misreads her silent prayer at first, then blesses her, and the LORD opens her womb. Samuel is born, weaned, and brought to the sanctuary as a living answer to prayer."]'::jsonb,
  'Saul becomes desperate when the Philistines gather and the LORD no longer answers him, so he disguises himself and seeks a medium at Endor. The woman summons Samuel, who rebukes Saul and repeats that the LORD has torn the kingdom away from him. Saul hears the sentence of death before returning to face the battle.',
  'This advanced summary best matches 1 Samuel 28 (1 Samuel 28:1-7-1 Samuel 28:1-25).'
WHERE NOT EXISTS (
